                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 12: Market regulator Sebi has proposed to relax the disclosure norms for rights issues to help shareholders retain their stake and reduce the overall cost of issuance. The announcement comes at a time when companies are preferring other modes of raising capital post-IPO. Sebi said it might not be necessary to mandate exhaustive disclosure requirements.                             
	 New York, March 12: Global credit rating agency Standard amp; Poors has lowered the long-term debt rating of General Electric and its finance units, while maintaining a stable outlook for the diversified conglomerate. The rating was lowered by one notch from AAA to AA+.                            
	 Mumbai, March 12: The Reserve Bank of India has appointed global consultancy firm Ernst amp; Young to assess the performance of its senior executives, primarily in the rank of chief general managers.                             
	 New York, March 12: Wall Street conman Bernard Madoff was led handcuffed to jail today after pleading guilty to tricking thousands of people out of billions of dollars in one of historys biggest financial scams.                                                                                                                                               
